<DocsLayout title="Installation" description="Getting started with rs-grid">
  <h1>Getting started</h1>
  <p class="lead">
    Add rs-grid to a Leptos CSR project in a few steps. You'll need Rust,
    wasm-pack or Trunk, and a Leptos project.
  </p>

  <h2>Prerequisites</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Rust toolchain (stable, 2021 edition)</li>
    <li><a href="https://trunkrs.dev" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Trunk</a> for building and serving</li>
    <li>The <code>wasm32-unknown-unknown</code> target</li>
  </ul>
  <pre><code>rustup target add wasm32-unknown-unknown</code></pre>

  <h2>Add the dependency</h2>
  <p>
    Add <code>rs-grid-leptos</code> to your <code>Cargo.toml</code>. While the
    crate is not yet published to crates.io, reference it by path:
  </p>
  <pre><code>[dependencies]
rs-grid-leptos = &#123; path = "../rs-grid-leptos" &#125;</code></pre>

  <h2>Basic usage</h2>
  <p>Import the component and mount it inside a Leptos view:</p>
  <pre><code>use leptos::*;
use rs_grid_leptos::GridCanvas;

#[component]
pub fn App() -&gt; impl IntoView &#123;
    view! &#123;
        &lt;GridCanvas
            rows=1_000_000
            cols=50
        /&gt;
    &#125;
&#125;</code></pre>

  <h2>Run locally</h2>
  <p>Start the development server from the example directory:</p>
  <pre><code>cd examples/basic-leptos
trunk serve</code></pre>
  <p>Open <code>http://localhost:8080</code> in your browser.</p>

  <h2>Build for production</h2>
  <pre><code>cd examples/basic-leptos
trunk build --release</code></pre>
  <p>
    The output goes into <code>dist/</code>. Serve it with any static file
    server or use the provided Docker image.
  </p>

  <h2>Workspace commands</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Command</th><th>Description</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>cargo check --workspace</code></td><td>Quick type-check of all crates</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>cargo test --workspace</code></td><td>Run all unit tests</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>cargo fmt --all</code></td><td>Format the entire workspace</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>cargo clippy --workspace -- -D warnings</code></td><td>Lint with warnings as errors</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</DocsLayout>
